Issues.Body:
Fixes #17332

This PR ensures that keyframes are emitted even when they are referenced following a comma, e.g.:

```css
@theme {
  --animate-test: 500ms both fade-in, 1000ms linear 500ms spin infinite;
                                 /* ^ */

  @keyframes fade-in {
    from {
      opacity: 0%;
    }
    to {
      opacity: 100%;
    }
  }
}
```

## Test plan

Added a unit test to capture the issue from #17332

This PR adds support for literal values inside the `--value('…')` and `--modifier('…')` functions. This allows you to safelist some known values you want to use:

E.g.:

```css
@utility tab-* {
  tab-size: --value('revert', 'initial');
}
```

This allows you to use `tab-revert` and `tab-initial` for example.
